xxl.core.cursors.wrappers
Class IteratorEnumeration

java.lang.Object
  xxl.core.cursors.wrappers.IteratorEnumeration
All Implemented Interfaces:
Enumeration
public class IteratorEnumeration
extends Object
implements Enumeration

The iterator-enumeration wraps an iterator to an enumeration, i.e., the wrapped iterator can be accessed via the methods of the enumeration interface. Therefore the methods hasMoreElements and nextElement have to be implemented as follows: 

     public boolean hasMoreElements() {
         return iterator.hasNext();
     }
 
     public Object nextElement() throws NoSuchElementException {
         return iterator.next();
     }
The required functionality is delivered by applying the methods hasNext and next to the given iterator.
